1
00:00:20,708 --> 00:00:21,583
Fuck.s

2
00:00:27,958 --> 00:00:29,958
Fuck me. You caught two?

3
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:35,250
Sir, want to buy a lottery ticket?

4
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:38,750
Do I look lucky to you?
I haven't caught a thing.

5
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,208
Ask someone else.

6
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:45,958
Might as well buy one.
Your luck could change.

7
00:00:46,958 --> 00:00:48,666
See my face?

8
00:00:49,166 --> 00:00:50,166
Look lucky to you?

9
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:57,125
Meeting me was lucky.
I have a powerful amulet.

10
00:00:57,791 --> 00:01:01,750
Guarantee it'll turn your luck around.

11
00:01:03,083 --> 00:01:04,500
Keep it for yourself.

12
00:01:05,625 --> 00:01:06,625
Don't believe me?

13
00:01:10,916 --> 00:01:11,750
How about this?

14
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:16,375
If it doesn't work, you'll be doing me
a favor taking it off my hands.

15
00:01:16,875 --> 00:01:18,375
But if it does,

16
00:01:20,041 --> 00:01:21,041
come work for me.

17
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:22,958
The hell you talking about?

18
00:01:32,333 --> 00:01:35,291
AGENT FROM ABOVE

19
00:01:37,083 --> 00:01:41,375
A LIFETIME OF LUCK

20
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:07,541
-The demon's coming.
-No riding in the corridor.

21
00:02:08,625 --> 00:02:09,875
Wang Hsiao-ming!

22
00:02:09,958 --> 00:02:13,083
-You're supposed to be the adult here.
-He started it, not me.

23
00:02:13,166 --> 00:02:14,500
It's all your fault.

24
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,250
You still at it?

25
00:02:19,083 --> 00:02:21,208
The demon's coming.

26
00:02:25,958 --> 00:02:28,041
-I'm going.
-Take care.

27
00:03:04,458 --> 00:03:05,583
Old guard. Delivery.

28
00:03:07,625 --> 00:03:08,458
Thank you.

29
00:03:26,791 --> 00:03:28,166
FEITI TEMPLE

30
00:03:35,208 --> 00:03:37,125
Brother Yu, Silly Chiang is back.

31
00:03:38,458 --> 00:03:40,625
Brother Yu. Look.

32
00:03:44,208 --> 00:03:45,125
I'm telling you,

33
00:03:46,041 --> 00:03:49,041
I'm on such a roll. It's like I'm blessed.

34
00:03:51,250 --> 00:03:53,708
This lucky amulet
is bringing you good luck.

35
00:03:56,666 --> 00:04:00,041
Bro, what else can I do now I'm so lucky?

36
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:02,750
Chiang.

37
00:04:03,291 --> 00:04:08,166
With such good luck,
you should be asking what can't you do?

38
00:04:11,625 --> 00:04:13,333
Right. I'll get going then.

39
00:04:22,875 --> 00:04:25,625
DONGFENG MARKET

40
00:04:31,208 --> 00:04:34,625
I told you to hide it properly.
Who's to blame now it's been stolen?

41
00:04:35,958 --> 00:04:37,416
Damn, it must be Wu Tien-chi.

42
00:04:39,458 --> 00:04:42,000
He sent someone to steal it
as soon as we found it.

43
00:04:42,083 --> 00:04:43,000
What does that prove?

44
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:46,625
He's desperate.

45
00:04:47,625 --> 00:04:50,000
Of course he's desperate.

46
00:04:50,750 --> 00:04:52,125
Did you find the thief yet?

47
00:04:53,958 --> 00:04:57,958
Su Chih-chiang, aka Silly Chiang.
Prior convictions for gambling and theft.

48
00:04:58,041 --> 00:05:01,083
Silly enough to leave fingerprints
when he's got a record.

49
00:05:02,166 --> 00:05:03,083
Got an address?

50
00:05:12,125 --> 00:05:15,875
I checked the surveillance footage.
He always comes here.

51
00:05:15,958 --> 00:05:17,125
He loves to gamble.

52
00:05:27,291 --> 00:05:28,833
Yes, I won again.

53
00:05:34,958 --> 00:05:35,791
Look.

54
00:05:36,833 --> 00:05:38,458
I'm winning big time.

55
00:05:39,125 --> 00:05:41,333
-Why does he always win?
-Look.

56
00:05:41,958 --> 00:05:43,250
It can't be down to luck.

57
00:05:44,083 --> 00:05:46,916
Either he's cheating
or he's running some kind of scam.

58
00:05:50,916 --> 00:05:54,750
Chao says they're already outside.
All the exits are blocked.

59
00:05:55,583 --> 00:05:56,625
Let's get him.

60
00:05:56,708 --> 00:05:58,916
It's the jackpot… It's gonna be mine…

61
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:02,791
I got it! Look.

62
00:06:02,875 --> 00:06:04,958
-I hit it big!
-Look, incredible!

63
00:06:05,958 --> 00:06:07,291
-Police.
-Scram!

64
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:08,583
Fuck.

65
00:06:10,125 --> 00:06:11,208
Trying to run?

66
00:06:17,125 --> 00:06:18,166
Out of the way!

67
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:26,541
-Stop!
-What the heck?

68
00:06:28,916 --> 00:06:30,000
I'm sorry.

69
00:06:38,083 --> 00:06:38,958
Come catch me!

70
00:06:44,708 --> 00:06:46,375
You got a death wish?

71
00:06:55,416 --> 00:06:57,208
-Where are you going?
-Let go.

72
00:06:57,291 --> 00:06:59,500
-Where's the incense burner?
-Let go.

73
00:07:02,666 --> 00:07:03,500
Serves you right.

74
00:07:07,166 --> 00:07:08,000
Get up…

75
00:07:10,375 --> 00:07:13,125
Where did you go? Where's Chao?

76
00:07:13,208 --> 00:07:16,625
Not here. I sent the wrong address.
He really tore me a new one.

77
00:07:18,166 --> 00:07:21,208
-Fuck.
-Damn it, how are we this unlucky?

78
00:07:21,708 --> 00:07:24,125
-The stars are against us.
-Or Mercury in retrograde.

79
00:07:24,208 --> 00:07:26,958
-So what should we do?
-Eat some lucky pork noodles.

80
00:07:57,791 --> 00:08:00,583
WANG YU-CHING:

81
00:08:00,666 --> 00:08:03,583
I'M ALMOST THERE
LET'S GRAB A SNACK

82
00:08:16,458 --> 00:08:18,416
-Hello?
-Mr. Wang.

83
00:08:19,375 --> 00:08:21,000
You're the guy from last time.

84
00:08:21,083 --> 00:08:23,375
You let that thug Hsieh Kun-hao get away.

85
00:08:23,458 --> 00:08:24,833
The police let him go.

86
00:08:24,916 --> 00:08:27,750
They said he has nothing to do
with her disappearance

87
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,375
Why would you believe them?

88
00:08:32,041 --> 00:08:35,541
They never took this case seriously.

89
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,875
Your daughter is outside Water Gate No. 7.

90
00:08:41,958 --> 00:08:43,375
Go now.

91
00:08:43,458 --> 00:08:45,583
Or it'll be too late.

92
00:09:03,916 --> 00:09:05,500
-You reported it?
-Yes.

93
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:08,375
The body's over there.

94
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:17,833
Thanks.

95
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:27,208
Chang Min,
this is the info we have so far.

96
00:09:29,708 --> 00:09:30,541
Chao.

97
00:09:31,208 --> 00:09:34,833
Jane Doe, about the same age
as Wang Yu-ching.

98
00:09:34,916 --> 00:09:38,291
But there's no head.
We'll need the DNA analysis to know more.

99
00:09:39,125 --> 00:09:42,833
-Stop! This is a crime scene.
-Sir! What are you doing?

100
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:45,041
-Fuck.
-Hey, stop him.

101
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:46,750
Mr. Wang.

102
00:09:48,708 --> 00:09:50,583
-Mr. Wang.
-Is it Ching?

103
00:09:50,666 --> 00:09:52,666
-She's the same age.
-Tell me. Is it her?

104
00:09:52,750 --> 00:09:55,625
-But it might not be her.
-Calm down, Mr. Wang.

105
00:09:55,708 --> 00:09:56,541
Calm down.

106
00:09:56,625 --> 00:09:58,875
-Is it her?
-We don't know for sure.

107
00:09:58,958 --> 00:10:00,875
Mr. Wang, calm down first.

108
00:10:07,541 --> 00:10:09,500
What use are the police?

109
00:10:11,541 --> 00:10:13,625
Aren't you supposed to catch the bad guys?

110
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:18,375
Aren't you supposed to
bring criminals to justice?

111
00:10:18,458 --> 00:10:20,000
You useless piece of shit!

112
00:10:20,083 --> 00:10:21,833
You're all useless!

113
00:10:23,958 --> 00:10:25,833
My daughter's dead because of you.

114
00:10:27,083 --> 00:10:29,250
She's dead because of you.

115
00:10:38,083 --> 00:10:39,375
I'm going to kill him.

116
00:10:40,041 --> 00:10:41,250
I'm going to kill him.

117
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:43,291
Damn it. It's all your fault.

118
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:46,416
It's all your fault.

119
00:10:53,625 --> 00:10:56,375
I'm going to kill him!

120
00:11:04,458 --> 00:11:09,000
Boss, I got the incense burner.
What should I do next?

121
00:11:09,083 --> 00:11:12,416
Look after it for me.
Don't let Han Chieh find it.

122
00:11:12,958 --> 00:11:14,333
Okay, got it.

123
00:11:15,708 --> 00:11:16,916
Also…

124
00:11:18,208 --> 00:11:19,833
You could…

125
00:11:21,583 --> 00:11:25,625
Stir things up at Dongfeng Market.
Keep Han Chieh busy for me.

126
00:11:26,625 --> 00:11:29,208
No problem. That's my area of expertise.

127
00:11:42,791 --> 00:11:45,500
Hi, Little Leafy. We meet again.

128
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:48,375
-Waiting for Chieh?
-Yeah.

129
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:51,958
He seems in a pretty bad mood today.
I don't dare go upstairs.

130
00:11:52,041 --> 00:11:54,750
Oh please, he just likes to act all moody.

131
00:11:54,833 --> 00:11:57,083
He's a big softie really.

132
00:11:59,083 --> 00:12:03,375
I used to have a psychopathic sugar daddy
who'd beat me for no reason.

133
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:05,666
I couldn't take it,
so I tried to leave him.

134
00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:11,125
But that psychopath wouldn't let me go.
Chieh helped me deal with him in the end.

135
00:12:11,208 --> 00:12:12,416
Why aren't you together?

136
00:12:15,958 --> 00:12:21,041
Things are pretty chill
between us right now. It suits us both.

137
00:12:32,208 --> 00:12:34,000
Is that a wig you're wearing?

138
00:12:35,458 --> 00:12:36,500
Yeah.

139
00:12:37,708 --> 00:12:38,791
From the chemo.

140
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:52,166
In all the years I've known Chieh,
I've only ever seen him fall for one girl.

141
00:12:52,875 --> 00:12:55,250
She was sick like you.

142
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:57,416
Huh?

143
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:00,041
She was terminally ill.

144
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:03,416
You know,
Chieh tried to take his own life.

145
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:05,875
She didn't have much time left.

146
00:13:06,458 --> 00:13:08,875
They both lost hope in life,

147
00:13:09,458 --> 00:13:11,625
yet still wanted something to hold onto.

148
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:15,625
Chieh stayed with her
until her time was up.

149
00:13:17,166 --> 00:13:22,208
Since then, he's never gotten
seriously involved with another girl.

150
00:13:23,083 --> 00:13:24,708
He'd rather pay for it.

151
00:13:26,708 --> 00:13:28,083
It keeps things simpler.

152
00:13:42,166 --> 00:13:44,041
Wow, look.

153
00:13:46,375 --> 00:13:47,208
Incredible…

154
00:13:48,166 --> 00:13:50,958
Come on, to us. Cheers.

155
00:13:51,041 --> 00:13:54,916
A TV, air-con, deck chairs.
I even got a coconut tree for you.

156
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,708
This isn't hell. It's basically a resort.

157
00:14:00,083 --> 00:14:03,791
Kid, you've worked hard
to rack up merit with me over the years.

158
00:14:03,875 --> 00:14:07,583
But you never use it on yourself.
I find that interesting.

159
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:17,208
I owe them this.

160
00:14:18,625 --> 00:14:20,833
Besides, the Demon King's new agent
is tough.

161
00:14:20,916 --> 00:14:23,125
I'll probably settle down here soon too.

162
00:14:23,958 --> 00:14:25,041
Settle down, my ass.

163
00:14:25,125 --> 00:14:26,750
I want you all in on this.

164
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:30,791
I didn't choose you
for being young and a good fighter.

165
00:14:31,958 --> 00:14:33,416
Then why did you choose me?

166
00:14:35,083 --> 00:14:36,166
Take a guess.

167
00:14:52,416 --> 00:14:53,250
Han Chieh.

168
00:14:55,208 --> 00:14:56,541
Why are you here again?

169
00:14:56,625 --> 00:15:01,166
Mei-na and I are eating with Sister Lo,
then I'm playing games with the old guard.

170
00:15:02,583 --> 00:15:04,666
-You're keeping busy.
-Yep.

171
00:15:11,833 --> 00:15:14,291
Everything all right? How are you feeling?

172
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:16,583
I'm fine.

173
00:15:17,083 --> 00:15:19,541
You're the one acting all weird and moody.

174
00:15:19,625 --> 00:15:23,166
I don't even dare feed Javvy,
in case I annoy you.

175
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,583
I've got so much going on.

176
00:15:27,916 --> 00:15:29,250
It's driving me nuts.

177
00:15:39,708 --> 00:15:40,708
What?

178
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:42,708
Han Chieh.

179
00:15:43,458 --> 00:15:46,958
If I get a boyfriend someday,
I hope he's just like you.

180
00:15:51,541 --> 00:15:55,625
And I thought you were just an idiot.
Turns out you're an idiot with bad taste.

181
00:16:02,583 --> 00:16:05,583
Chieh! Someone's causing trouble.
Go and help the old guard.

182
00:16:09,208 --> 00:16:12,458
How dare you touch my stuff?
I'll kick your ass!

183
00:16:29,375 --> 00:16:33,041
Chieh, these hooligans
want to have a barbecue on the rooftop.

184
00:16:33,125 --> 00:16:36,791
They even demanded
that you have a drink with them.

185
00:16:36,875 --> 00:16:38,500
-I…
-Old guard!

186
00:16:39,125 --> 00:16:40,000
I…

187
00:16:42,916 --> 00:16:43,958
A barbecue upstairs?

188
00:16:44,041 --> 00:16:44,916
FEITI TEMPLE

189
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,125
You have to defeat me first.

190
00:16:52,458 --> 00:16:56,125
You're Han Chieh, right?
What've you done to piss off the big man?

191
00:16:56,208 --> 00:16:57,208
The big man?

192
00:16:57,291 --> 00:17:00,791
I don't usually piss off any big men,
just scumbags down below.

193
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:01,916
Finish him.

194
00:17:11,958 --> 00:17:13,333
Wang Hsiao-ming!

195
00:17:16,208 --> 00:17:18,250
-What?
-What are you doing?

196
00:17:18,333 --> 00:17:20,125
What the fuck? Are you blind?

197
00:17:20,208 --> 00:17:21,916
-What? It wasn't me.
-Fuck you.

198
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:25,000
Granny said this is our turf
and I should scare them off.

199
00:17:25,083 --> 00:17:27,208
-She'll take responsibility.
-How?

200
00:17:27,291 --> 00:17:28,625
I'll get back to it.

201
00:17:30,750 --> 00:17:31,958
Not again!

202
00:17:34,541 --> 00:17:35,416
Damn you.

203
00:17:37,833 --> 00:17:39,750
-Old guard.
-Little punk.

204
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:42,083
What the hell? Fuck.

205
00:17:42,958 --> 00:17:45,125
-What the hell?
-Kill him!

206
00:17:45,208 --> 00:17:46,291
Charge!

207
00:17:46,375 --> 00:17:48,250
-Naughty boys.
-Dare show up here?

208
00:17:48,333 --> 00:17:51,291
Don't run. Come here.
I'm going to kill you.

209
00:17:54,791 --> 00:17:56,791
Enough… Stop hitting me…

210
00:17:58,208 --> 00:18:01,125
Take this! And this!

211
00:18:03,291 --> 00:18:05,583
I've got you. Can't run now.

212
00:18:05,666 --> 00:18:07,875
-Just you try.
-You won't get away.

213
00:18:07,958 --> 00:18:09,208
What do you want?

214
00:18:09,291 --> 00:18:10,833
Who sent you here?

215
00:18:10,916 --> 00:18:13,750
Are you stupid?
I wouldn't tell you even if I knew.

216
00:18:13,833 --> 00:18:15,750
What an embarrassment.

217
00:18:15,833 --> 00:18:16,708
Let's go!

218
00:18:17,708 --> 00:18:18,583
Come on.

219
00:18:20,291 --> 00:18:21,916
Get lost!

220
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:28,125
-Look at them run.
-Don't you dare come back.

221
00:18:39,583 --> 00:18:43,500
-What? Haven't you done enough fighting?
-There's another one, one more.

222
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:48,166
Haven't you taken enough?

223
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:49,500
Okay… Right away…

224
00:18:49,583 --> 00:18:50,500
Hurry up.

225
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,083
What happened?

226
00:18:58,208 --> 00:18:59,833
Some troublemakers turned up.

227
00:19:00,583 --> 00:19:01,625
Why are you here?

228
00:19:02,125 --> 00:19:04,333
We found a Jane Doe this morning.

229
00:19:04,416 --> 00:19:06,583
Age and appearance match Wang Yu-ching.

230
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:08,208
Is it her?

231
00:19:08,291 --> 00:19:10,750
Not sure yet.
We're waiting for the DNA report.

232
00:19:10,833 --> 00:19:15,375
But if it is her, then the final sacrifice
for the array must be someone else.

233
00:19:15,458 --> 00:19:18,041
The full moon is in three days.
What should we do?

234
00:19:19,125 --> 00:19:21,625
-One more.
-Think they can mess with us? No chance.

235
00:19:21,708 --> 00:19:24,083
Humans and ghosts
are united in Dongfeng Market.

236
00:19:24,166 --> 00:19:28,083
We sent those punks packing in no time.

237
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:33,250
The magic array was complete,
but he was waiting

238
00:19:33,333 --> 00:19:36,041
for midnight
when the moon is at its height.

239
00:19:36,125 --> 00:19:39,541
Only then could he regain his full power
through the array portal.

240
00:19:39,625 --> 00:19:41,083
Where's the portal?

241
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:43,500
At the center of the array,

242
00:19:44,500 --> 00:19:45,416
Dongfeng Market.

243
00:19:47,166 --> 00:19:49,333
-The other side…
-The other side? Okay…

244
00:19:49,416 --> 00:19:52,041
Better not think of coming back
while we're here.

245
00:19:55,083 --> 00:19:56,916
-Harder.
-The back too…

246
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:57,875
The back.

247
00:20:00,041 --> 00:20:01,833
-Harder.
-That's it, squeeze…

248
00:20:04,541 --> 00:20:05,375
Everyone.

249
00:20:10,416 --> 00:20:13,625
I wanted to tell you individually,
but since you're all here,

250
00:20:14,875 --> 00:20:16,500
I may as well tell you all.

251
00:20:23,791 --> 00:20:27,500
A demon is coming for me
and coming for Dongfeng Market.

252
00:20:28,708 --> 00:20:33,000
For everyone's safety, I want you
to leave Dongfeng Market for a while.

253
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:38,041
I'll stay and protect
the ghosts who can't leave.

254
00:20:41,291 --> 00:20:44,250
You want us to go
and leave you here all by yourself?

255
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:47,875
I'm the Third Crown Prince's agent.
I have to stay.

256
00:20:51,875 --> 00:20:53,250
If I defeat him,

